fields.value: Census of Population and Housing, 1980: Summary Tape File 1

dsDescriptionValue.value:
Summary tape file 1 A,B,C contains identical tables and formats. They differ only in geographic coverage.

The files contain complete-count data. Population items tabulated include age, race (provisional data), sex, marital status, Spanish origin (provisional data), household type, and household relationship. Housing items tabulated include occupancy/vacancy status, tenure, contract rent, value, condominium status, number or rooms, and plumbing facilities. Selected aggregates, means, and medians are also provided. Data are presented in 59 tables consisting of 321 cells.

FILE A provides summaries for the State, county, MCDs, CCDs, places or their equivalents, census tracts or BNAs, and BGs or, enumeration districts. Summaries (provided in hierarchical sequence) are also presented on File A for places and congressional districts (96th Congress). FILE B provides summaries in hierarchical sequence for States, SMSAs, nonSMSA remainder of State, counties, MCDs within counties (20 States), or places within counties (30 States), census tracts or BNAs, and blocks or EDs. Data for SMSA's which cross State lines are shown only for that portion in the particular State file. Summaries are also provided for partially block-numbered portions of all geographic levels. FILE C (also referred to as the National file) has summaries for: U.S., census regions, census divisions, States, standard consolidated statistical areas, standard metropolitan statistical areas, and urbanized areas. SCSA's, SMSA's or UA's which cross State lines also have a record for the SCSA, SMSA, or UA portion within each State. Summaries are included for counties, places of 10,000 or more population, MCD's of 10,000 or more population in eleven selected States, and congressional districts. Puerto Rico and other outlying areas are excluded from File C.
